&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Early Intervention Practitioner&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;North Somerset Early Intervention in Psychosis Service&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The provision of Early Intervention Services is a priority for the Trust. This is an exciting opportunity for practitioners with experience and enthusiasm in delivering psychosocial interventions to contribute to the provision of services for young people and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team provides a comprehensive range of interventions to individuals who experience or who are at high risk of experiencing first episode psychosis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post involves the care coordination for people experiencing their first episode of psychosis. You will be an RMN, familiar with delivering psychosocial interventions to individuals experiencing psychosis symptoms and their families. This will involve one to one, group work and co-working with families. You will be committed to a recovery based approach promoting social inclusion. You will be enthusiastic about making links with colleagues as well as other agencies and have an interest in talking to groups of people about psychosis. You will be working closely with the other Early Intervention Workers and members of the local Recovery and Intensive Support Teams and the inpatient unit. This post will be based at the Coast Resource Centre in Worle, Weston-super-Mare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Team base is close to junction 21 of the M5 and has excellent transport links with Bristol.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Julia Mortimer – Team Manager 01934 523700 julia.mortimer@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Louise Hamilton – Senior Practitioner Tel 01934 523700 e-mail louise.hamilton2@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
